On to the Update:

Grok-3
------

From Bloomberg ( https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2025-02-18/musk-s-=
xai-debuts-grok-3-ai-bot-touting-benchmark-superiority ) :

Elon Musk=E2=80=99s artificial intelligence startup xAI showed off the upda=
ted Grok-3 model, showcasing a version of the chatbot technology that the b=
illionaire has said is the =E2=80=9Csmartest AI on Earth.=E2=80=9D Across m=
ath, science and coding benchmarks, Grok-3 beats Alphabet Inc.=E2=80=99s Go=
ogle Gemini, DeepSeek=E2=80=99s V3 model, Anthropic=E2=80=99s Claude and Op=
enAI=E2=80=99s GPT- 4o , the company said via a live stream on Monday. Grok=
-3 has =E2=80=9Cmore than 10 times=E2=80=9D the compute power of its predec=
essor and completed pre-training in early January, Musk said in a presentat=
ion alongside three of xAI=E2=80=99s engineers. =E2=80=9CWe=E2=80=99re cont=
inually improving the models every day, and literally within 24 hours, you=
=E2=80=99ll see improvements,=E2=80=9D Musk said.

The company introduced a new smart search engine with Grok-3 , calling it D=
eepSearch. DeepSearch is a reasoning chatbot that expresses its process of =
understanding a query and how it plans its response. It includes options fo=
r research, brainstorming and data analysis, the demonstration showed. Musk=
=E2=80=99s team also said it intends to release a voice-based chatbot =E2=
=80=9Cas soon as possible.=E2=80=9D

Grok-3 appears to be one of if not the best-performing base model in the wo=
rld; it is topping the usual benchmarks ( https://x.com/amasad/status/18917=
09057238507526?s=3D46 ) (but not if you include o3 ( https://x.com/12exyz/s=
tatus/1891723056931827959 ) ), and tops all categories with the highest eve=
r score in LMArena ( https://x.com/lmarena_ai/status/1891706264800936307 ) =
, an increasingly difficult feat ( https://x.com/GavinSBaker/status/1891723=
733976465420 ) as models have converged in the GPT-4 class. Andrew Karpathy=
 is not an objective observer =E2=80=94 he is the former Senior Director of=
 AI at Tesla =E2=80=94 but his review on X ( https://x.com/karpathy/status/=
1891720635363254772 ) is worth a read; some highlights:

The impression overall I got here is that this is somewhere around o1-pro c=
apability, and ahead of DeepSeek-R1 , though of course we need actual, real=
 evaluations to look at=E2=80=A6

The impression I get of DeepSearch is that it's approximately around Perple=
xity DeepResearch offering (which is great!), but not yet at the level of O=
penAI's recently released "Deep Research", which still feels more thorough =
and reliable=E2=80=A6

As far as a quick vibe check over ~2 hours this morning, Grok 3 + Thinking =
feels somewhere around the state of the art territory of OpenAI's strongest=
 models ( o1 -pro, $200/month), and slightly better than DeepSeek -R1 and G=
emini 2.0 Flash Thinking. Which is quite incredible considering that the te=
am started from scratch ~1 year ago, this timescale to state of the art ter=
ritory is unprecedented.

This gets at the first Grok-3 takeaway: it is simultaneously surprising and=
 not surprising. Start with the latter: xAI famously built a 100,000 GPU da=
ta center in Memphis (and now has 200,000 ( https://x.com/NinaDSchick/statu=
s/1891711656234975410 ) GPUs), and used 20,000 GPUs to train Grok-3 ; that'=
s the largest cluster ever and, sure enough, it resulted in a top tier mode=
l. That's not surprising given it is what scaling laws predicted, but it is=
 comforting, as there was a question as to whether scaling laws had hit a w=
all.

What is surprising is that xAI is only 19 months old: the company has gone =
from incorporation to largest GPU cluster in the world to arguably the best=
 model in less time than it has taken OpenAI to go from GPT-4 to GPT-5 (alb=
eit with substantial updates along the way, including a big 4o update just =
this past weekend). That is certainly a testament to both Elon Musk and his=
 team =E2=80=94 just ask Nvidia CEO Jensen Huang ( https://www.youtube.com/=
watch?v=3DlpLFjQ-bRv8 ) =E2=80=94 and to the fact that not only are models =
commoditizing, but so is the knowledge of how and the wherewithal to build =
them.

